.TH OTPCLIENT 1 "April 2026" "otpclient" "OTPClient Manual"
.SH NAME
otpclient \- GTK4 / libadwaita client for TOTP and HOTP one-time passwords
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B otpclient
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B OTPClient
is a GTK4 / libadwaita application that generates Time-based (TOTP) and
HMAC-based (HOTP) one-time passwords. The encrypted token database is
stored on disk using AES-256-GCM with an Argon2id-derived key.
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 3
TOTP and HOTP support.
.IP \(bu 3
Custom digits (4-10), period (1-300 s), and algorithm (SHA1, SHA256, SHA512).
.IP \(bu 3
Steam-style codes.
.IP \(bu 3
Manage multiple databases and switch between them.
.IP \(bu 3
Per-token grouping with filterable views.
.IP \(bu 3
Import and export Aegis (plain or encrypted), AuthPro (plain or encrypted),
2FAS (plain or encrypted), FreeOTP+ (plain), and Google Authenticator QR
codes (file or live capture).
.IP \(bu 3
Add new tokens manually, by scanning a QR code from a file, or via the
device camera.
.IP \(bu 3
Auto-lock after a configurable inactivity timeout, on screensaver
activation, or on demand.
.IP \(bu 3
Optional integration with the system Secret Service for keyring-stored
database passwords (also enables cross-database search).
.IP \(bu 3
Optional GNOME Shell / KDE KRunner search provider that surfaces tokens
in the system search results.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.var/app/com.github.paolostivanin.OTPClient/config/otpclient/otpclient.cfg
Flatpak configuration file (when running under Flatpak).
.TP
.I ~/.config/otpclient/otpclient.cfg
Configuration file containing the path to the active database.
.TP
GSettings schema
.I com.github.paolostivanin.OTPClient
Stores user preferences (theme, auto-lock, notifications, KDF parameters, etc.).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Honoured by GLib for locating the configuration file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR otpclient-cli (1)
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/paolostivanin/OTPClient/issues
